Source : https://www.ioi-jp.org/camp/2017/2017-sp_camp-kumabe2.pdf
Any graph G = (V, E)

If (i, j) is in E and i < j, then Aij = xij
If (i, j) is in E and i > j, then Aij = -xji
Other Aij = 0

det(A) != 0 <=> G has a perfect matching
(rank(A) / 2 = the maximum size of matching)

In practical use, let xij be random numbers
